des: "This a fantastic old-fashioned sugar cookie recipe that is not as sweet as others that I have used.  They complement a powdered sugar icing without being overly sweet.  My favorite, and EASY!"
ins:
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C).
Cream sugar and shortening together.  Add eggs and dry ingredients.  Add the milk last.
No need to chill this dough, simply roll out to 1/4 inch thickness, cut out and bake 10-12 minutes.
